This paper deals with image denoising, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of graph Laplacian regularization, which is a popular technique in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which are relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents an iterative algorithm for image denoising, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
